article.headline: Vanderbilt 78, No. 12 Oklahoma 66
article.story:
NASHVILLE, Tenn. --  Jasmine Lister scored 24 points, Christina Foggie added 21 and Vanderbilt remained unbeaten by handing No. 12 Oklahoma its first loss, a 78-66 defeat in the Vanderbilt Thanksgiving Tournament on Saturday.

Sophomore Aaryn Ellenberg scored 13 straight points including a trio of 3-pointers down the stretch and finished with 22 for the Sooners (3-1).

Foggie reeled off 18 first-half points and hit four 3-pointers in the first 11 minutes for the Commodores (6-0). Lister took over after halftime, scoring nine points, including a 3 in a 16-7 Vanderbilt run that opened a 55-46 lead.

Morgan Hook added 16 points with three 3-pointers for Oklahoma, and Joanna McFarland had 10 points and 10 rebounds.

Lister went out briefly with leg cramps with about 12 minutes left after her reverse fastbreak layup against McFarland capped a 9-2 spurt following Tiffany Clarke's block. But Hook then hit her second 3-pointer of the half to draw Oklahoma within 55-49.

Freshman Maggie Morrison responded with her second 3-pointer of the half to push the Commodores' lead back to nine. Lister's 3-pointer with 7 1/2 minutes remaining gave the Commodores a 61-51 lead.
